Algorithm 2: Sugeno integrals using fuzzy membership function for decision-level fusion

Input:
- A set of crisp values X = {x1, x2, ..., xn} representing the input values
- A set of fuzzy membership functions μ1, μ2, ..., μm defined on X

Output:
- A single crisp value representing the Sugeno integral of the fuzzy membership functions

Begin
    Input the fuzzy membership function values for each element in the input set.
    Initialize the numerator and denominator of the Sugeno integral to zero.
    
    For each fuzzy membership function μi,
        Calculate the degree of membership mi(xi) for each input value xi in X.
        
    For each input value xi in X,
        Calculate the weighted value wi = μi(xi) * xi for each fuzzy membership function μi.
        
    Sum the weighted values wi for each fuzzy membership function μi.
    Sum the degrees of membership mi(xi) for each input value xi in X.
    
    Divide the sum of the weighted values by the sum of the degrees of membership.
    
End For

Return the Sugeno integral value as the output.
End
